```julia
using Jchemo, JchemoData
using JLD2, CairoMakie
```

#### Data importation

```julia
using JchemoData, JLD2, CairoMakie
path_jdat = dirname(dirname(pathof(JchemoData)))
db = joinpath(path_jdat, "data/cassav.jld2")
@load db dat
@names dat
```

```julia
X = dat.X
@head X
```

```julia
Y = dat.Y
@head Y
```

```julia
year = Y.year 
tab(year)
```

```julia
s = year .<= 2012
Xtrain = X[s, :] 
Xtest = rmrow(X, s) 
ntot = nro(X) 
ntrain = nro(Xtrain) 
ntest = nro(Xtest)
(ntot = ntot, ntrain, ntest)
```

#### Model fitting and scores T

```julia
model0 = pcasvd(nlv = 10) 
fit!(model0, Xtrain)  
fitm0 = model0.fitm 
@names fitm0
```
#### SD-OD space

It can be useful to plot the score vs. orthogonal distances (SD and OD, respectively) to check that the training and test sets share the same 
space. This can be implemented by using function `occsdod` (one-class classification with SD and OD). 

**OCC model fitting** 

```julia
model = occsdod()
fit!(model, fitm0, Xtrain)
fitm = model.fitm
@names fitm
@head dtrain = fitm.d
```

**Prediction on test** 

```julia
res = predict(model, Xtest)
@names res
@head dtest = res.d
```

**Final graph** 

```julia 
d = vcat(dtrain, dtest)
group = [repeat(["Train"], ntrain); repeat(["Test"], ntest)]
color = [(:red, .5), (:blue, .5)]
plotxy(d.d_sd, d.d_od, group; zeros = true, color, xlabel = "SD", ylabel = "OD").f
```

